5 people were killed on Penge road, Limpopo on Saturday.It is alleged that a combi and a Suzuki collided head-on along Penge road in Tubatse policing area.The accident happened late on yesterday next to Annesley mine killing five people instantly.Police Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe says all five people in the Suzuki were killed and the taxi was travelling from Burgersfort while the Suzuki was going to the opposite direction.&#8220;The five deceased are age between 22 and 25 years old and they were all passengers of the Suzuki and all victims who were in the combi were taken to Dilokong hospital with serious injuries for medical treatment,&#8221; she said.The cause of the accident is unknown as the police investigations are ongoing.TNA Reporter 